How To Make Admin User

Go into database:

docker exec -it hotel_db psql -U postgres -d hotel_booking


Then run:

UPDATE "User"
SET role = 'ADMIN'
WHERE email = 'test@example2.com';


If successful, you will see:

UPDATE 1


That means 1 row updated.

🔎 Verify

Run:

SELECT email, role FROM "User";


You should see:

test@example2.com | ADMIN

🔥 IMPORTANT

Now you must LOGIN AGAIN.

Because your old JWT token still contains:

role: USER


JWT tokens are static after created.

So:

Login again

Get new accessToken

Call admin route with new token

🎯 Expected Result

Now:

GET /bookings/admin/all


Should return booking data (or empty array).

No 401.
No 403.

🧠 What You Just Learned

401 = no token
403 = wrong role
200 = correct role

That is professional backend auth flow.